Update German translation

Remove the line wrap on the allow_sub_dir option

This was intended for very long translation strings,
but it does more harm than good.

Add some spacing

Visually group related option blocks.

Change a request to a hint

As of commit 81107ed8ab7247ac44347bbf36bba8636cb6b431 the "Open with"
dialog can be used to open other file types, making xdg-open just an
alternative to self-selection.

Do not display copyright information on the console anymore

This is to dissociate this fork from the source version and
to emphasize its independence.

Also, change MAINTAINER_YEAR to indicate the constant revision.

Remove pointless GTK_DIALOG_DESTROY_WITH_PARENT flag

The dialogs are explicitly destroyed upon completion.

Remove pointless GTK_DIALOG_DESTROY_WITH_PARENT flag

There is no parent, and the dialog is explicitly destroyed
when the program ends.

Remove the pointless calls to gtk_window_set_destroy_with_parent()

There is not yet a parent at the time of creation, and the dialogs
are explicitly destroyed when the program ends.

Change the expand argument when calling gtk_box_pack_start()

If the box has the homogeneous property set, and therefore all children
have the same size, the child must expand (which also happens implicitly
with FALSE as an argument, but it is more obvious this way).

Change an effectless argument when calling gtk_box_pack_start()

The argument has no effect if the preceding argument is set to FALSE.

Revise the design of the options page of the add dialog

Make the compression frame less high, increase the top padding of its
contents a bit, and decrease the top padding of the "No compression"
button.

This way the minimum height of the two bottom frames can be smaller.

Also, remove a call to gtk_button_set_alignment() which has no effect.
Use size GTK_ICON_SIZE_BUTTON for button images

Revise the creation of the file button in xa_show_archive_comment()

This makes the code easier to read.

Revise the creation of the select button in xa_select_by_pattern_dialog()

This makes the code easier to read.

Do not use 0.0 as an argument

Take advantage of automatic conversion.

Do not unnecessarily create alignments with special values

Use the default values if the special values have no effect at all.

Free config_file and xdg_open after freeing prefs_window

Both are related to the preferences dialog.

Rename the dialog_data structs

Their declarations now read more like those of GTK widgets.

Use GTK_STOCK macros as argument when creating dialogs

Also, indent properly.

Revise xa_create_prefs_dialog()

Make the code easier to read.

Also, prevent the icon view window from expanding horizontally, add
some padding to the right, and increase the size of the combo boxes
on the Advanced page.

Rename parameters

Use the same type parameter names that are used
for the add and extract dialog functions.

Clean up the use of local variables in xa_create_prefs_dialog()

Reduce the excessive use of GtkWiget pointers by reusing them.
It is not necessary to use a separate pointer for each new widget.

Also, rearrange variable definitions.
Fix memory leaks
Rename Prefs_dialog_data members related to window geometry and size

Sort Prefs_dialog_data members

This corresponds to how they appear in the dialog.

Remove unnecessary Prefs_dialog_data members

They do not need to be accessed.

Rename some Prefs_dialog_data members

Make it easier to read by removing unnecessary numbering
and choosing simpler and more correct names.

Also, rename the local variable pointing to the allocated
Prefs_dialog_data memory to prefs_dialog.
